summary:
“Dan and Phil announced the movie premiere in Brazil yesterday 😁.
Some people were mad about it though. What do you think?” From...
body:
“Dan and Phil announced the movie premiere in Brazil yesterday 😁.

Some people were mad about it though. What do you think?” From @existencial-coop-doop

I think it’s nice of them to actually go the extra effort to organise it, considering this was an ongoing agreement with the venue there could have been limited dates for them to be able to book. However also something like this was expected of them because of the TBC dates, which on its own is a touchy subject. Therefore the set dates could have been the latest available for the rest of the year, or that actually fits into DNP’s schedules. However it’s understandable that people are mad, whether it’s finding the money for the tickets/traveling/places to stay or it not working with their plans, because that can be a stressful process, which correlates to that fact that people could be disappointed when after all this they still can’t attend it. But as it was an ongoing thing they did do the right thing by announcing it in the livestream the week before, as then it gives people pre-warning that this is a thing that is going to be happening in the near future, but I do agree that is often not enough time for people.

I understand why people are mad. On the other hand though Dan and Phil were trying to do it for a whole year and even after tour they still tried to do something for Brazil and Mexico while some people would probably just leave it. It’s not their fault really. I’m happy for the people who are able to go but at the same time I’m sad that not everyone would be able to see them
